Ariel Sharon's appointment as the Israeli foreign minister serves as ``the bullet of mercy'' for the Middle East peace process, an official Syrian newspaper said Saturday. 1984-90: Serves as trade minister in national unity government headed by Yitzhak Shamir of Likud and Shimon Peres of Labor. 1990-92: Serves as housing minister, presiding over settlement drive in the West Bank and Gaza Strip. 1996: Named infrastructure minister in Netanyahu government. Oct. 9, 1998: Netanyahu appoints him foreign minister, places him in charge of negotiations with the Palestinians, marking his return to the center of Israeli politics and world political arena. 